claim: Marcus Aurelius's Meditations is considered to be a literary monument to Stoic philosophy.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Aurelius ' Meditations , written in Greek while on campaign between 170 and 180 , is still revered as a literary monument to a philosophy of service and duty , describing how to find and preserve equanimity , a state of psychological stability and composure , in the midst of conflict by following nature as a source of guidance and inspiration .

premise_source_doc_sentence: Meditations  (  -LSB- Τὰ εἰς ἑαυτόν , Ta eis heauton -RSB- , literally '' -LSB- that which is -RSB- to himself ''  )  is a series of personal writings by Marcus Aurelius , Roman Emperor from 161 to 180 AD , recording his private notes to himself and ideas on Stoic philosophy .
